Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Java Developer* position with *HYR Global Source Inc*. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack web applications, RESTful APIs, and microservices architecture, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed and developed RESTful APIs and microservices that translate natural-language intents into validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints, requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and safe execution across a distributed microservices surface. I built Java-based generative code solutions including RESTful API-aware templates, SDK patterns, and code-generation workflows to accelerate platform API integration and improve implementation correctness. To keep these systems production-ready, I enabled robust observability using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing, structured logs, and evaluation hooks to troubleshoot and debug failures, collaborating with cross-functional teams to optimize application performance and reducing latency by 60% and API costs by 50% through best practices in system design. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to the backbone infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform using React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications with clean, efficient code. I integrated RESTful APIs and services across the platform, collaborating with cross-functional teams to deliver features while ensuring best practices through code reviews. I also developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions to handle long-running data import jobs and prevent AWS Lambda timeouts, optimizing application performance and scalability. Together, these roles have prepared me to design, develop, and maintain high-performance Java-based applications and contribute meaningfully to your team's core engineering responsibilities.

